      text: [
        "我小时候住在一座小城里，城里没有工厂，所以也没有机器的声音。我那时以为凡能发出声音的，都是活的生物。",
        "可是父亲怀里的表有时放在桌子上，不但它的秒针会自己走动，而且它坚硬的表盖里还会发出清脆的声音：嘀嗒，嘀嗒……没有一刻的休息。",
        "一天，我对父亲说：\u201C我爱听这表的声音。\u201D我一边说一边向着表伸出手去。父亲立刻把我的手拦住了，他说：\u201C只许听，不许动。\u201D",
        "他这么说，就更增加了表的神秘。\u201C不许动\u201D，里边该是什么东西在响呢？我想：表里边一定也有一个蝉或虫一类的生物吧。",
        "有一次，父亲对我笑着说：\u201C你来，我给你看看表里是什么在响，可是只许看，不许动。\u201D父亲取出一把小刀，把表盖拨开，我的面前立即呈现出一个美丽的世界：蓝色的、红色的小宝石，钉住几个金黄色的齿轮，里边还有一个小尾巴似的东西不停地摆来摆去。",
        "\u201C这摆来摆去的是一个小蝎子的尾巴，一动就要蜇你。\u201D",
        "我吓了一跳，蝎子是多么丑恶而恐怖的东西，为什么把它放在这样一个美丽的世界里呢？但是我也感到愉快，证实我的猜测没有错：表里边有一个活的生物。",
        "后来我见人就说：\u201C我有蟋蟀在钵子里，蝈蝈在葫芦里，鸟儿在笼子里，父亲却有一个小蝎子在表里。\u201D\n这样的话我不知说了多久，也不知道到什么时候才不说了。"
      ],
      textEn: [
        "When I was small, I lived in a town without factories or the sound of machines. I believed that everything that made sound was alive.",
        "But Father's watch, sometimes left on the table, not only had a moving second hand, but from within its hard case came a clear, crisp sound: tick-tock, tick-tock — never stopping.",
        "One day, I said to Father: 'I love listening to the sound of this watch.' As I spoke, I reached my hand toward it. Father immediately stopped my hand and said: 'You may listen, but you may not touch it.'",
        "This made the watch even more mysterious. 'Not allowed to touch' — what could be making the sound inside? I thought there must be some kind of cicada or insect living in there.",
        "Once, Father smiled and said: 'Come, I'll show you what's making the sound, but you may only look, not touch.' He opened the case with a small knife, and a beautiful little world appeared before me: tiny blue and red gemstones holding golden gears, and a small tail-like thing swinging back and forth without stopping.",
        "'That swinging thing is a little scorpion's tail — touch it and it'll sting you.'",
        "I was startled — scorpions are ugly, terrifying creatures! Why would one be inside such a beautiful world? But I was also pleased, because my guess was confirmed: there was a living creature inside the watch.",
        "After that I told everyone: 'I keep crickets in a jar, katydids in a gourd, birds in a cage, but my father has a little scorpion in his watch.'\nI don't know how long I kept saying this, or when I finally stopped."
      ],
      writeChars: ["脆","拦","玻","璃","恶","怖"],
